item.title: GA’s Martin Escobari on AI Fueling New Opportunities
item.description: General Atlantic Co-President Martin Escobari tells Bloomberg Surveillance that the AI-driven digital transformation and recent market stress are creating new opportunities - but with US assets expensive, he sees global diversification as essential amid rising uncertainty. Escobari speaks to Bloomberg TV on the sidelines of the 2026 World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland. (Source: Bloomberg)
item.category: PEOPLE NEWS — Personnel Moves in Industrial Brokerage/Development

item.title: CoreWeave CEO Intrator on AI Demand, Infrastructure Strain and Skepticism
item.description: CoreWeave CEO Michael Intrator discusses surging AI demand, infrastructure development, the company’s biggest constraints and growing skepticism in the sector. He speaks with Bloomberg Television on the sidelines of the 2026 World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland. (Source: Bloomberg)
item.category: PEOPLE NEWS — Personnel Moves in Industrial Brokerage/Development

item.title: Danish Pension Fund AkademikerPension to Exit US Treasuries
item.description: The Danish pension fund AkademikerPension is planning to exit US Treasuries by the end of the month, amid concerns that the policies of President Donald Trump have created credit risks too big to ignore.
